# Documentation and reports placement

When the user asks to **write a report**, **save a specification**, or **document** something:

1. Open and follow **docs/DOCUMENTATION_RULES.md** (section «Для AI / агента»).
2. Put backend-related reports in **backend/docs/reports/YYYY-MM-DD__topic-name.md**.
3. Put Harvester/AI-pipeline reports in **ai-pipeline/harvester/docs/reports/YYYY-MM-DD__topic-name.md**.
4. Put cross-project specs and architecture in **docs/** (repo root).
5. Put backend runbooks/checklists in **backend/docs/**; Harvester specs in **ai-pipeline/harvester/docs/**.

Report filenames: `YYYY-MM-DD__name.md` (two underscores, Latin, hyphens). Include at the top: date, git commit, scope, source of truth (e.g. docs/Navigator_Core_Model_and_API.md).
